00:44:13.610 --> 00:44:19.330
So I was just in Texas this
weekend, and I was at some

00:44:19.330 --> 00:44:22.760
markets where they have their
own freshly made tortillas,

00:44:22.760 --> 00:44:25.580
where they produce their
own fresh masa.

00:44:25.580 --> 00:44:29.750
So I think these days--

00:44:29.750 --> 00:44:32.830
I mean, it's fabulous if you
can find fresh corn masa.

00:44:32.830 --> 00:44:35.190
And maybe in San Francisco,
there is.

00:44:35.190 --> 00:44:40.930
I wouldn't tell anybody to grind
the corn and cook it for

00:44:40.930 --> 00:44:46.370
48 hours with lime, and then
peel it, and then kneel down

00:44:46.370 --> 00:44:48.410
on the floor, and make a masa.

00:44:48.410 --> 00:44:53.900
It is great if you can find
somebody to do that in a

00:44:53.900 --> 00:44:54.630
tortilleria.

00:44:54.630 --> 00:44:59.050
But if you don't, you can buy
the corn masa flour and just

00:44:59.050 --> 00:45:01.500
mix it with water and a
little bit of salt.

00:45:01.500 --> 00:45:03.490
And it is really good quality.

00:45:03.490 --> 00:45:11.060
So you can have fresh-made masa
in the fast way, which

00:45:11.060 --> 00:45:14.070
honestly, is what Mexican
peoples do in their homes in

00:45:14.070 --> 00:45:16.740
Mexico, when they don't have
access to a tortilleria.

00:45:16.740 --> 00:45:18.230
Everybody uses those.

00:45:18.230 --> 00:45:21.430
You know, Maseca or
a masa like that.

00:45:21.430 --> 00:45:23.570
You buy it, and it's
really delicious.

00:45:23.570 --> 00:45:26.590
So there are things in the book
where I use fresh masa.

00:45:26.590 --> 00:45:32.150
Like there's some chochoyotes,
some dumplings, that go into a

00:45:32.150 --> 00:45:35.060
very easy yellow mole.

00:45:35.060 --> 00:45:37.450
I also show people, if
they want to make

00:45:37.450 --> 00:45:39.790
their own corn tortillas.

00:45:39.790 --> 00:45:41.290
But it is not crucial.

00:45:41.290 --> 00:45:44.360
There's a thousand gazillion
things that you can make

00:45:44.360 --> 00:45:47.800
without fresh masa.

